  "prompt": "Why is it that Battlefield 4 on PS3 only has 24 players in one game when DICE said that it will support 32?",
  "response": "The discrepancy between the promised 32 players and the actual 24-player limit on PS3 for Battlefield 4 was due to the hardware limitations of the PlayStation 3. While DICE initially aimed to support 32 players, the PS3's older hardware couldn't effectively handle that many players in a single match without significant performance issues. \n\nThe 24-player limit was a compromise to maintain acceptable performance, frame rates, and overall gameplay experience on the aging PS3 hardware. In contrast, next-gen consoles (PS4 and Xbox One) and PC versions were able to support the full 32-player count more effectively.\n\nThis was a common issue during the cross-generation period, where game developers had to balance performance and feature sets between older and newer hardware platforms.",
